6
00:00:16,570 --> 00:00:18,340
There is a limit to one's frivolity!

7
00:00:18,340 --> 00:00:20,220
I won't allow you to divorce!

8
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:22,080
Withdraw the application right away!

9
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:24,310
I'm sorry.

10
00:00:24,310 --> 00:00:26,670
The divorce application...

11
00:00:26,670 --> 00:00:28,000
has already been-

12
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,470
I'll definitely not allow it!

13
00:00:32,750 --> 00:00:34,660
I'm holding a family meeting.

14
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:37,090
Go get your mom.

15
00:00:38,180 --> 00:00:40,270
- Divorced?
- Divorced?

16
00:00:40,270 --> 00:00:42,450
Don't tell me, Koichi was cheating on you?

17
00:00:42,450 --> 00:00:45,180
Of course not. He's not like you, Dad.

18
00:00:45,180 --> 00:00:48,840
Look, our relationship is turning into something new that we've never experienced-

19
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:50,280
I don't care anymore.

20
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:52,040
That's harsh.

21
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:53,970
Then, why?

22
00:00:53,970 --> 00:00:57,710
Koichi has been assigned to live near the base,

23
00:00:57,710 --> 00:01:00,290
while I'm not able to leave Tokyo, so...

24
00:01:00,290 --> 00:01:01,940
So you both got a divorce?

25
00:01:01,940 --> 00:01:05,280
I can't help it. There are other factors contributing to it as well.

26
00:01:05,280 --> 00:01:06,940
That's outrageous.

27
00:01:06,940 --> 00:01:09,170
Ask Koichi to come over now. I'll give him a talking-to.

28
00:01:09,170 --> 00:01:11,040
I wonder who's the one who needs a talking-to.

29
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:13,340
Of course, the one who's talking right now.

30
00:01:13,340 --> 00:01:16,600
Well, I never expected it to turn out well in the first place.

31
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:17,820
How could you say that?

32
00:01:17,820 --> 00:01:20,920
I support Saki's divorce.

33
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:24,740
A divorce is not necessarily a bad thing.

34
00:01:24,740 --> 00:01:28,330
It can also allow you to move on.

35
00:01:28,330 --> 00:01:30,380
Mom.

36
00:01:31,610 --> 00:01:34,430
Huh? I wonder who it is.

37
00:01:34,430 --> 00:01:35,990
It must be a woman, isn't it?

38
00:01:35,990 --> 00:01:37,210
Azusa!

39
00:01:37,210 --> 00:01:38,170
No, it's not!

40
00:01:38,170 --> 00:01:40,000
Look, it's Obara.

41
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,180
<i>[Tadashi Obara]</i>

42
00:01:41,180 --> 00:01:45,040
Hi, hello there. This is Mizuguchi.

43
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:47,700
It's still "Obara".

44
00:01:51,350 --> 00:01:52,350
Please come in.

45
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:53,960
Please, excuse us.

