- Sorry about it!
- Sorry about it!

51
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,250
Well...

52
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:28,620
We are terribly sorry

53
00:02:28,620 --> 00:02:29,990
that your daughter has been deflowered!

54
00:02:29,990 --> 00:02:31,750
- Deflowered?
- Well, well.

55
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:33,470
What era are we living in now?

56
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:36,290
This is the Reiwa period, you know?

57
00:02:36,290 --> 00:02:39,530
I'm sure Saki also must have said it wilfully.

58
00:02:39,530 --> 00:02:43,340
No, when such things happen, the man should take responsibility.

59
00:02:43,340 --> 00:02:46,670
Anyway, I will definitely not allow this divorce to happen!

60
00:02:46,670 --> 00:02:48,540
Please reconsider it.

61
00:02:48,540 --> 00:02:50,660
Are you still having second thoughts?

62
00:02:50,660 --> 00:02:54,220
Or both of you were waiting for the other to initiate giving up the idea of divorce?

63
00:02:54,220 --> 00:02:57,180
I personally feel that Koichi is a good man.

64
00:02:57,180 --> 00:03:01,550
He's serious, he's serious...

65
00:03:01,550 --> 00:03:04,580
He's serious...

66
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:11,150
I feel the same too! He is serious...

67
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:13,850
He is serious and a good man, isn't he?

68
00:03:13,850 --> 00:03:16,270
He takes very good care of Saki.

69
00:03:16,270 --> 00:03:22,330
I also felt very relieved that Koichi can be together with a girl like Saki.

70
00:03:22,330 --> 00:03:25,960
That is why we went ahead with our own divorce.

71
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:27,920
- Divorce?
- Divorce?

72
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:31,080
You've finally signed the divorce papers?

73
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:33,390
We, ourselves, are also divorced.

74
00:03:33,390 --> 00:03:37,180
That's why we don't really have much right to say anything.

75
00:03:37,180 --> 00:03:40,550
We have been married for 40 years!

76
00:03:40,550 --> 00:03:41,760
There's nothing wrong about that!

77
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:46,100
Actually... we both are also divorced.

78
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,870
What?

79
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:50,390
Regretful, isn't it?

80
00:03:50,390 --> 00:03:51,920
Very... regretful.

81
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:52,890
Me, me, me!

82
00:03:52,890 --> 00:03:54,090
I'm also getting divorced.

83
00:03:54,090 --> 00:03:55,160
- What?
- What?

84
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:56,580
What is this... all of a sudden?

85
00:03:56,580 --> 00:03:59,740
You certainly can't have a divorce!

86
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:02,700
Why is the one who's getting divorced objecting to mine?

87
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:05,230
But there's Azusa to think about, don't you, Kaede?

88
00:04:05,230 --> 00:04:08,680
When a child is involved, it's a different matter altogether, right?

89
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:11,690
Azusa is only nine, isn't she?

90
00:04:11,690 --> 00:04:14,890
It's all right, Midori. I'm fine.

91
00:04:14,890 --> 00:04:18,150
I'm the most mature one among everybody here.

92
00:04:18,150 --> 00:04:19,610
Azusa!

93
00:04:19,610 --> 00:04:25,180
Divorced, divorced, divorced!

94
00:04:25,180 --> 00:04:28,730
Aren't you all a family of divorcees? Think about it.

95
00:04:29,980 --> 00:04:34,140
A family of divorcees.

96
00:04:34,140 --> 00:04:36,260
That's true.

97
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,330
Ridiculous!

98
00:04:38,330 --> 00:04:40,650
We can't face our ancestors like this.

99
00:04:40,650 --> 00:04:42,150
Make up with each other, both of you!

100
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:44,400
You are right.

101
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:48,280
An entire family of divorcees is a little too...

102
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:50,610
I am sorry.

103
00:04:51,390 --> 00:04:54,010
No matter how much you object to it,

104
00:04:54,010 --> 00:04:56,450
my feelings...

105
00:04:56,450 --> 00:05:00,090
will not waver even one tiny bit.

106
00:05:00,090 --> 00:05:01,720
What?

107
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:09,230
I-I...

108
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:12,230
will...

109
00:05:13,190 --> 00:05:15,830
live my life separately from Saki.

110
00:05:21,490 --> 00:05:23,520
I, too...

111
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:26,890
will live my life separately from Koichi.

112
00:05:29,020 --> 00:05:33,780
Once Koichi says something, he is the type to not retract it.

113
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:37,520
Are you really fine with that, Saki?

114
00:05:39,590 --> 00:05:41,640
Koichi...

115
00:05:43,050 --> 00:05:46,630
often does this when he can't sort out his feelings.

116
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:50,030
He has always been like this ever since he was a child.

117
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:57,710
If you ever have any problems, just tell me anytime.

118
00:05:57,710 --> 00:05:59,550
Thank you very much.

119
00:05:59,550 --> 00:06:00,740
Hey!

120
00:06:00,740 --> 00:06:02,290
Hurry up.

121
00:06:02,290 --> 00:06:04,710
I'm heading that way.

122
00:06:33,150 --> 00:06:34,920
I'm sorry...

123
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:37,680
for coming over uninvited.

124
00:06:41,780 --> 00:06:44,720
We have already announced to our families about our divorce,

125
00:06:45,510 --> 00:06:47,350
so this...

126
00:06:48,260 --> 00:06:50,690
is really the last time we will meet.

127
00:06:57,440 --> 00:06:58,630
- Actually-
- What is it?

128
00:06:58,630 --> 00:07:01,180
Sure.

129
00:07:01,180 --> 00:07:05,060
Okay. I'll be there at 10, tomorrow morning.

130
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:06,960
Thank you, Ryan.

131
00:07:07,860 --> 00:07:09,310
Bye.

132
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:13,190
Well then...

133
00:07:13,190 --> 00:07:15,640
let me say this.

134
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,530
Take care.

135
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:21,590
You too,

136
00:07:21,590 --> 00:07:23,480
take care.

137
