144
00:07:49,890 --> 00:07:51,920
Antonio.

145
00:08:02,460 --> 00:08:06,440
<i>[How to Get a Divorce for the Whole Family!]</i>

146
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:07,930
<i>[Episode 7]</i>

147
00:08:07,930 --> 00:08:10,060
- Hey, Takaya.
- Yes?

148
00:08:10,060 --> 00:08:13,430
Shall I tell you some interesting news?

149
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:15,750
Saki and Koichi...

150
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:18,410
have officially divorced!

151
00:08:18,410 --> 00:08:22,320
Both of them declared they would be living their lives apart from each other.

152
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,440
Azusa!

153
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:25,610
Go to your room.

154
00:08:25,610 --> 00:08:28,690
I take this as a forcible removal of a danger hazard.

155
00:08:28,690 --> 00:08:30,220
Hey!

156
00:08:31,510 --> 00:08:34,010
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

157
00:08:35,370 --> 00:08:39,590
Well then... please let me know the reason for wanting a divorce.

158
00:08:39,590 --> 00:08:41,580
He... has a mother complex.

159
00:08:41,580 --> 00:08:42,600
Mother complex?

160
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:48,230
His mom said she will look after Azusa, and suggested moving in to live with us.

161
00:08:48,230 --> 00:08:50,400
That man only listens to his mom.

162
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:55,020
At this rate, I feel Azusa will be taken away from me. That's why I took her with me and left.

163
00:08:55,020 --> 00:09:00,260
In general, the party who lives together with the child tends to have a higher chance of parental custody.

164
00:09:00,260 --> 00:09:02,120
I'm glad to hear that!

165
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,920
I will negotiate with them.

166
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:07,420
You and Azusa can leave it to me.

167
00:09:07,420 --> 00:09:11,130
Thank you. I'm glad that you are here, Takaya.

168
00:09:11,130 --> 00:09:12,690
No problem.

169
00:09:12,690 --> 00:09:16,130
We can always count on you, as always.

170
00:09:16,130 --> 00:09:19,900
Hey. Can we stay over here for the time being?

171
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:23,910
I've used up quite a bit of my savings bunking in hotels.

172
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:26,600
You have an empty room available, don't you?

173
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,470
Can I stay over too?

174
00:09:28,470 --> 00:09:30,210
Huh? Why?

175
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:33,750
I thought you rented an apartment, Mom?

176
00:09:34,610 --> 00:09:36,890
Because I'm worried about all of you.

177
00:09:36,890 --> 00:09:40,940
But you're okay with that? You may want to discuss this with your boyfriend.

178
00:09:40,940 --> 00:09:42,280
Boyfriend?

179
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:43,740
Who? From where?

180
00:09:43,740 --> 00:09:46,400
The editor, Tachikawa.

181
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:48,240
It's him?

182
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:51,320
If it's him, I certainly won't allow it.

183
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:53,740
You, too, have Macaron Lady, don't you?

184
00:09:53,740 --> 00:09:57,780
Come on, you've split up already, so stop quarreling.

185
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:03,010
I feel embarrassed you had to see that.

186
00:10:03,010 --> 00:10:05,480
I'm somewhat envious of such lively banter.

187
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:07,970
There's nothing to be envious about.

188
00:10:07,970 --> 00:10:11,530
It seems like a lot is going on. Are you all right?

189
00:10:11,530 --> 00:10:14,570
Yes. I'm fine.

190
00:10:15,410 --> 00:10:17,610
I'm ready to listen anytime.

191
00:10:18,450 --> 00:10:20,010
Thank you.

192
00:10:20,010 --> 00:10:22,810
But... I'm fine.

193
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:01,370
<i>[Art Editorial Department]</i>

194
00:11:03,710 --> 00:11:05,420
Hi, Chief.

195
00:11:05,420 --> 00:11:06,780
Yes?

196
00:11:06,780 --> 00:11:08,360
I...

197
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:12,000
have changed my name back to Saki Mizuguchi.

198
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,290
What?

199
00:11:13,860 --> 00:11:15,720
<i>[Certificate of Change in Name]</i>

200
00:11:17,250 --> 00:11:20,040
I'm divorced, that's why...

201
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:24,020
To have your name changed back so soon,

202
00:11:24,020 --> 00:11:27,140
sounds a little embarrassing, don't you think?

203
00:11:28,430 --> 00:11:30,490
There's no shame...

204
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:32,700
in being divorced.

205
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:35,450
"A divorce is ultimately a natural phenomenon,

206
00:11:35,450 --> 00:11:38,900
that lays asleep between husband and wife in many families."

207
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:41,780
As quoted by Sebastien Chamfort.

208
00:11:41,780 --> 00:11:44,870
Any couple will have a contemplated divorce at least once in their lives. And you,

209
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:48,530
all you did was merely execute it.

210
00:11:51,150 --> 00:11:55,580
- One! Two! Three! Four!
- One! Two! Three! Four!

211
00:11:55,580 --> 00:11:57,210
- Five! Six!
- Five! Six!

212
00:11:57,210 --> 00:11:59,110
How many more times till we're done?

213
00:11:59,110 --> 00:12:00,120
Tani.

214
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:03,550
There's no limit to an emergency rescue! Don't be naive!

215
00:12:13,580 --> 00:12:15,750
Let's start our mini briefing.

216
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:17,480
Yes, sir!

217
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,830
Before that...

218
00:12:21,830 --> 00:12:25,500
I have... an announcement to make.

219
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:27,420
Oh, what is it?

220
00:12:28,540 --> 00:12:30,460
I...

221
00:12:30,460 --> 00:12:32,920
- am divorced.
- What?

222
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:33,980
- Divorced?
-  Divorced?

223
00:12:33,980 --> 00:12:36,250
I am very sorry...

224
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:39,360
that things have come to this.

225
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:45,070
This is the congratulatory gift that I received from all of you.

226
00:12:45,070 --> 00:12:47,710
Commander, please accept it.

227
00:12:47,710 --> 00:12:50,090
No way I can do that!

228
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,710
Second Lieutenant Ichinose.

229
00:12:53,710 --> 00:12:55,470
No.

230
00:12:55,470 --> 00:12:57,010
Saotome.

231
00:12:58,430 --> 00:13:00,460
- Tani.
- I've given it away, so...

232
00:13:00,460 --> 00:13:02,610
- Kariba.
- I cannot accept it!

233
00:13:02,610 --> 00:13:04,470
Y-you're right.

234
00:13:04,470 --> 00:13:07,550
I will feel bad if you don't accept it!

235
00:13:07,550 --> 00:13:10,430
Have you carefully thought about it?

236
00:13:12,220 --> 00:13:13,890
I do not have any regrets.

237
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:18,580
To me now, focusing on my work is most important.

238
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:21,640
You're divorced?

239
00:13:21,640 --> 00:13:22,960
Yes.

240
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:27,160
You... didn't mention that you placed a bet on this marriage.

241
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:29,770
No, I didn't.

242
00:13:30,380 --> 00:13:33,130
I lost my bet.

243
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:37,480
Love doesn't exist in this world.

244
00:13:38,420 --> 00:13:40,320
Have you finally understood?

245
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:43,520
They're going to get divorced anyway,

246
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:46,400
so why did everyone get married then?

247
00:13:50,340 --> 00:13:51,920
Say...

248
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:54,420
You being divorced...

249
00:13:59,250 --> 00:14:02,840
means that there's no problem in crossing the line with me.

250
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:05,000
Well, that...

251
00:14:07,910 --> 00:14:09,900
I'm kidding.

252
00:14:18,450 --> 00:14:20,960
What a waste.

253
00:14:22,390 --> 00:14:25,180
A character like the rogue samurai,

254
00:14:25,180 --> 00:14:28,910
instead of arousing my interest as a writer,

255
00:14:28,910 --> 00:14:32,210
makes me want to, instead, observe him from nearby.

256
00:14:32,210 --> 00:14:33,930
Observe?

257
00:14:33,930 --> 00:14:39,050
The fact that you chose a wild-boar type of man as a marriage partner,

258
00:14:39,050 --> 00:14:42,870
makes me feel that you unexpectedly have a good eye.

259
00:14:58,580 --> 00:15:03,720
<i>[Family Rules]</i>

260
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,270
<i>What do you think of this?</i>

261
00:15:18,270 --> 00:15:21,860
<i>You two look perfect for each other.</i>

262
00:15:32,810 --> 00:15:36,690
Dear Saki.

263
00:15:37,490 --> 00:15:38,480
How...

264
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:43,160
are you?

265
00:15:44,850 --> 00:15:46,750
<i>How are you?</i>

266
00:15:57,490 --> 00:16:02,360
<i>[Dear Saki. How are you?]</i>

267
00:16:03,430 --> 00:16:04,860
<i>How are you?</i>

268
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:26,530
That move was rash!

269
00:16:31,750 --> 00:16:33,840
You were only thinking about checkmating.

270
00:16:33,840 --> 00:16:35,950
Shogi is not only about the individual.

271
00:16:35,950 --> 00:16:38,660
You must consider how the opponent will attack.

272
00:16:38,660 --> 00:16:41,490
That's the real thrill of playing it.

273
00:16:41,490 --> 00:16:42,690
Yes.

274
00:16:42,690 --> 00:16:45,260
It's not fun playing with you.

275
00:16:53,570 --> 00:16:55,520
Second Lieutenant Ichinose!

276
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:57,780
I'm sorry for the sudden visit!

277
00:17:00,670 --> 00:17:03,870
I've made too much Stewed Food.

278
00:17:03,870 --> 00:17:05,820
Please have some, if you don't mind.

279
00:17:05,820 --> 00:17:07,880
Thank you very much.

280
00:17:09,560 --> 00:17:11,820
- Well...
- W-Well...

281
00:17:11,820 --> 00:17:15,460
If you don't mind, would you like to come in?

282
00:17:15,460 --> 00:17:17,670
- Come in!
- Excuse me.

283
00:17:18,310 --> 00:17:20,750
- Who is she?
- She is Second Lieutenant Ichinose.

284
00:17:20,750 --> 00:17:23,300
She's a U.H. pilot and my superior.

285
00:17:23,300 --> 00:17:24,470
Really?

286
00:17:24,470 --> 00:17:27,720
I didn't realize you were Second Lieutenant. Please forgive me!

287
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:29,420
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

288
00:17:29,420 --> 00:17:30,870
Second Lieutenant...

289
00:17:30,870 --> 00:17:33,160
I have some good Japanese wine. Let me go get it!

290
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:36,280
- T-Thank you. I hope it is not too much trouble.
- No problem.

291
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:49,320
- It's delicious!
- Isn't it?

292
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:51,110
I'm glad.

293
00:17:51,620 --> 00:17:53,210
It's good!

294
00:17:57,250 --> 00:17:59,070
Mom.

295
00:17:59,070 --> 00:18:01,770
What is it all of a sudden? Did something happen?

296
00:18:01,770 --> 00:18:04,480
Sorry, I'm late.

297
00:18:05,510 --> 00:18:06,730
What?

298
00:18:06,730 --> 00:18:08,550
I asked Saki to come over.

299
00:18:08,550 --> 00:18:11,650
What? What is it?

300
00:18:12,370 --> 00:18:17,210
I... was robbed... of my 20 million.

301
00:18:17,210 --> 00:18:19,240
20 million?
<i>(T/N: About $158,000)</i>

302
00:18:22,670 --> 00:18:26,740
When did you realize that the money was gone?

303
00:18:27,390 --> 00:18:30,560
- Four, five days ago, I guess.
- What?

304
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:32,900
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

305
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:35,080
I couldn't tell you!

306
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:36,610
I didn't want you saying,

307
00:18:36,610 --> 00:18:39,720
"See? You got yourself a young boyfriend and he cheated on you!"

308
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:41,860
That would be so humiliating!

309
00:18:43,130 --> 00:18:47,960
Then, all those talks about stepping out into the world, were lies?

310
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:52,290
I couldn't contact him,

311
00:18:52,290 --> 00:18:55,420
my apartment contract was also dissolved.

312
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:08,750
I... I don't care anymore!

313
00:19:09,310 --> 00:19:11,590
Mom...

314
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:15,000
I give up. I'm totally defeated.

315
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,420
Don't say that.

316
00:19:16,420 --> 00:19:18,730
You were good, Second Lieutenant.

317
00:19:18,730 --> 00:19:22,430
Please don't call me that. Just call me Ichinose.

318
00:19:22,430 --> 00:19:24,190
Well then, Ichinose.

319
00:19:24,190 --> 00:19:28,400
Before taking on the Knight, if you had gotten rid of this Pawn,

320
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:31,070
we wouldn't know who will be the final winner.

321
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:33,700
I have learned something new.

322
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:37,920
But still, it was a great Shogi game.

323
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:41,010
You calmly assessed the war situation

324
00:19:41,010 --> 00:19:44,930
and made your killer move at the moment when the enemy least expected it.

325
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:49,040
This proves that you will make a fine commanding officer.

326
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:52,390
Thank you for such flattering compliments!

327
00:19:53,090 --> 00:19:55,110
Dad, your bath is ready.

328
00:19:55,110 --> 00:19:56,770
Is that so?

329
00:19:56,770 --> 00:19:58,810
Well then...

330
00:19:58,810 --> 00:20:01,650
I look forward to another game with you.

331
00:20:01,650 --> 00:20:03,310
I will not lose next time!

332
00:20:03,310 --> 00:20:06,570
That fighting spirit, I like it!

333
00:20:11,690 --> 00:20:15,150
I haven't seen my dad enjoying himself this much in a long time.

334
00:20:15,150 --> 00:20:17,140
Thank you very much.

335
00:20:17,140 --> 00:20:19,220
I also enjoyed myself.

336
00:20:19,220 --> 00:20:23,420
Thank you for the food. It was really delicious.

337
00:20:25,420 --> 00:20:29,870
I have something to tell you, Master Sergeant Obara.

338
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:33,050
What is it?

339
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:40,680
I would like to... report on the crimes that I have committed until now!

340
00:20:41,580 --> 00:20:43,170
First crime!

341
00:20:43,170 --> 00:20:47,710
At the barbecue party, the reason why your wife was lost,

342
00:20:47,710 --> 00:20:49,580
was because of me.

343
00:20:49,580 --> 00:20:51,060
Well... that happened a long time a-

344
00:20:51,060 --> 00:20:52,830
Next crime!

345
00:20:52,830 --> 00:20:54,690
At the recent party,

346
00:20:54,690 --> 00:20:59,580
I advised your wife to devote herself even more to you.

347
00:20:59,580 --> 00:21:03,460
Next crime! When Private Tani got injured,

348
00:21:03,460 --> 00:21:05,590
and your wife came to visit,

349
00:21:05,590 --> 00:21:07,620
I advised your wife...

350
00:21:07,620 --> 00:21:11,480
to divorce you!

351
00:21:12,560 --> 00:21:16,920
These are the three crimes I've committed, I am very sorry!

352
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:20,850
I will accept whatever punishment that you give me!

353
00:21:31,590 --> 00:21:33,700
It is my fault...

354
00:21:34,590 --> 00:21:37,840
that you and your wife are divorced.

355
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:39,630
You're wrong.

356
00:21:39,630 --> 00:21:41,700
The divorce...

357
00:21:43,270 --> 00:21:45,920
was decided between me and my wife.

358
00:21:46,540 --> 00:21:48,470
It is no fault of anybody's.

359
00:21:48,470 --> 00:21:50,320
Therefore...

360
00:21:50,320 --> 00:21:53,230
you don't have to apologize, Second Lieutenant Ichinose.

361
00:21:55,910 --> 00:21:57,420
Koichi!

362
00:21:57,420 --> 00:21:59,370
There's something wrong with the bath!

363
00:21:59,370 --> 00:22:00,830
I'm coming!

364
00:22:00,830 --> 00:22:02,190
W-Well then...

365
00:22:02,190 --> 00:22:06,970
I will resume our conversation another day.

366
00:22:08,780 --> 00:22:10,560
I'll take my leave.

367
00:22:11,510 --> 00:22:15,250
I'm sorry to keep troubling you.

368
00:22:16,180 --> 00:22:20,240
You keep having to see the embarrassing moments of my family.

369
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:22,100
Somehow...

370
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:24,390
I guess I can't help it.

371
00:22:24,390 --> 00:22:28,140
No family would want to air their dirty laundry in public.

372
00:22:28,140 --> 00:22:32,430
Even for me, when I was young, my parents had their problems too.

373
00:22:33,910 --> 00:22:38,470
It's very common for children to hide their true feelings for fear of hurting their parents.

374
00:22:39,100 --> 00:22:42,200
Do care more for Azusa too.

375
00:22:46,620 --> 00:22:49,250
Don't stress yourself too much.

376
00:22:49,910 --> 00:22:51,980
Relax a little, all right?

377
00:22:53,020 --> 00:22:57,470
Well, much to my own surprise, I'm feeling fine.

378
00:22:57,470 --> 00:22:59,060
I'll be all right.

379
00:23:01,140 --> 00:23:05,350
Don't put on that kind of facade in front of me.

380
00:23:06,630 --> 00:23:08,310
When the going got tough,

381
00:23:08,310 --> 00:23:11,640
you'd usually smile and say, "I'm fine."

382
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:17,280
How long do you think we were together?

383
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:19,990
Don't push yourself too hard. Just vent it all out

384
00:23:19,990 --> 00:23:22,180
because I've already seen everything.

385
00:23:23,180 --> 00:23:26,070
Come on, you should have heard of this fairy tale.

386
00:23:26,070 --> 00:23:30,780
"The King with Donkey Ears," where the king's secret was shouted into a hole.

387
00:23:30,780 --> 00:23:33,410
Think of me as the hole.

388
00:23:33,410 --> 00:23:35,170
If you please.

389
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:39,190
What is that?

390
00:23:39,780 --> 00:23:41,680
You finally smiled.

391
00:23:44,700 --> 00:23:46,990
I wanted to see that smile.

392
00:23:55,690 --> 00:23:58,870
- I'm home!
- Welcome back.

393
00:23:58,870 --> 00:24:00,650
Does it sting?

394
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:03,400
What happened?

395
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:07,130
She got into a fight at school.

396
00:24:07,130 --> 00:24:08,950
How come?

397
00:24:09,980 --> 00:24:12,330
She got into an argument with a friend,

398
00:24:12,330 --> 00:24:14,650
and the other party landed the first punch.

399
00:24:14,650 --> 00:24:17,400
Azusa retaliated and did the same.

400
00:24:31,230 --> 00:24:33,940
She has her problems too.

401
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,310
You know...

402
00:24:36,310 --> 00:24:40,940
I don't really have any memory of being hugged by Mom.

403
00:24:40,940 --> 00:24:44,120
It's all very vague to me.

404
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:47,170
I love Azusa too,

405
00:24:47,170 --> 00:24:49,330
but what should I do?

406
00:24:49,330 --> 00:24:51,920
Somehow, I can understand.

407
00:24:51,920 --> 00:24:56,320
Back in elementary school, even when it suddenly rained,

408
00:24:56,320 --> 00:24:59,860
- Mom never came to pick us up!
- Mom never came to pick us up!

409
00:25:01,140 --> 00:25:04,980
Mom was also trying her best to be a mom.

410
00:25:04,980 --> 00:25:09,320
Now I know. I was a kid then, so...

411
00:25:09,320 --> 00:25:10,860
You're right.

412
00:25:12,120 --> 00:25:14,950
I can also understand how you feel, Kaede.

413
00:25:14,950 --> 00:25:18,020
You didn't have the time to think about Azusa's feelings

414
00:25:18,020 --> 00:25:22,120
because your feelings are hurting too.

415
00:25:24,300 --> 00:25:25,580
Really...

416
00:25:25,580 --> 00:25:28,820
Marriage is something that's decided between two people,

417
00:25:28,820 --> 00:25:32,220
but a divorce drags a lot of people into it.

418
00:25:33,970 --> 00:25:37,500
I'll have a good talk with Azusa.

419
00:25:38,110 --> 00:25:40,720
Take your time to rest too, Sis.

420
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:43,490
You can stay here for as long as you like.

421
00:25:44,460 --> 00:25:47,250
Thanks, Saki.

422
00:25:50,980 --> 00:25:54,420
Time will heal all wounds.

423
00:25:55,150 --> 00:26:00,120
We will slowly forget those bad memories,

424
00:26:00,120 --> 00:26:02,410
and they will disappear with time.

425
00:26:03,220 --> 00:26:05,810
That's what they always say.

426
00:26:22,310 --> 00:26:27,280
<i>Will the happy memories also slowly disappear with time?</i>

427
00:26:31,660 --> 00:26:33,750
<i>Bit by bit.</i>

428
00:26:34,610 --> 00:26:36,680
<i>Disappear.</i>

429
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:39,580
<i>I'm glad...</i>

430
00:26:39,580 --> 00:26:43,980
<i>we could hang up these curtains as our last act together.</i>

431
00:26:43,980 --> 00:26:46,370
<i>Even after I'm gone,</i>

432
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:50,200
<i>at least...</i>

433
00:26:51,660 --> 00:26:54,580
<i>I hope they shall protect you.</i>

434
00:26:57,490 --> 00:26:59,480
<i>It feels as if...</i>

435
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:02,250
<i>they were not there to begin with.</i>

436
00:27:02,890 --> 00:27:04,660
<i>We're home!</i>

437
00:27:05,820 --> 00:27:08,480
<i>So this is how it turned out after you renovated it.</i>

438
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:10,390
<i>In the city, your parents' home is close by,</i>

439
00:27:10,390 --> 00:27:13,770
<i>so I felt you would feel safer living here.</i>

440
00:27:13,770 --> 00:27:17,100
<i>If you look at it... like this...</i>

441
00:27:41,440 --> 00:27:44,400
<i>[You have a new message.]</i>

442
00:27:47,460 --> 00:27:50,280
<i>Reason for divorce, number six.</i>

443
00:27:50,280 --> 00:27:53,290
<i>Your way of washing dishes is too soft.</i>

444
00:27:53,960 --> 00:27:56,270
I made sure to wash them cleanly.

445
00:27:56,270 --> 00:27:58,220
<i>I'll keep in mind the remaining 95 reasons,</i>

446
00:27:58,220 --> 00:28:01,760
<i>and s-send them to you by mail for sure. For sure!</i>

447
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:05,660
He really sent it over.

448
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:08,410
Seriously.

449
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:19,090
<i>Reason for divorce, number seven.</i>

450
00:28:19,090 --> 00:28:22,240
<i>You are too fixated on the method of washing dishes.</i>

451
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:25,580
<i>You should have washed them in the first place, then.</i>

452
00:28:39,070 --> 00:28:41,520
<i>Reason for divorce, number eight.</i>

453
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:43,050
<i>During our family meeting,</i>

454
00:28:43,050 --> 00:28:45,410
<i>although everyone said, "Koichi is a good man,"</i>

455
00:28:45,410 --> 00:28:47,670
<i>you didn't affirm it.</i>

456
00:28:57,070 --> 00:28:59,600
<i>Wouldn't it be weird if I affirmed it right there?</i>

457
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:02,320
<i>We were announcing our divorce, after all.</i>

458
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:09,590
<i>Those are two different matt-</i>

459
00:29:09,590 --> 00:29:13,650
<i>Even after we divorced, you still care so much about your image.</i>

460
00:29:13,650 --> 00:29:17,270
<i>I'm disappointed that you were thinking that way under that kind of situation.</i>

461
00:29:17,270 --> 00:29:18,420
<i>Same way goes for you.</i>

462
00:29:18,420 --> 00:29:22,880
<i>When they mentioned, "I am relieved that he was together with a girl like Saki,"</i>

463
00:29:22,880 --> 00:29:24,850
<i>don't you think you should have affirmed it?</i>

464
00:29:24,850 --> 00:29:26,630
Enough!

465
00:29:26,630 --> 00:29:28,380
<i>[Kouichi Obara : Incoming call]</i>

466
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:34,740
Hello?

467
00:29:34,740 --> 00:29:36,920
I've yet to type my reply,

468
00:29:36,920 --> 00:29:39,630
but your messages kept coming and coming and coming, non-stop and-

469
00:29:39,630 --> 00:29:41,840
I panicked.

470
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:46,060
I've noticed from the beginning that you're slow in typing.

471
00:29:48,230 --> 00:29:51,860
But... once you go to a location where there's no reception,

472
00:29:51,860 --> 00:29:55,280
those skills of yours will become useless!

473
00:29:55,280 --> 00:29:57,550
That's totally out of point.

474
00:29:57,550 --> 00:29:59,270
Reason for divorce, number nine.

475
00:29:59,270 --> 00:30:01,890
You laughed at my slowness in typing!

476
00:30:01,890 --> 00:30:03,990
Reason for divorce, number 10.

477
00:30:03,990 --> 00:30:05,470
You are petty.

478
00:30:05,470 --> 00:30:07,060
I'm not petty!

479
00:30:07,060 --> 00:30:09,690
See? You're seriously angry.

480
00:30:27,150 --> 00:30:31,160
Okay, then. I'll listen.

481
00:30:33,410 --> 00:30:35,890
How have you been?

482
00:30:39,740 --> 00:30:42,090
I'm doing well.

483
00:30:42,090 --> 00:30:43,850
How about you?

484
00:30:45,150 --> 00:30:47,840
No problem in particular.

485
00:30:49,670 --> 00:30:51,360
I'm glad to hear that.

486
00:30:55,780 --> 00:30:57,720
Actually...

487
00:31:01,310 --> 00:31:06,250
There are some things that I can't help but keep worrying about.

488
00:31:06,250 --> 00:31:08,140
What is it?

489
00:31:08,140 --> 00:31:10,330
I said

490
00:31:10,330 --> 00:31:13,420
that I would protect you forever,

491
00:31:13,950 --> 00:31:16,840
but I couldn't do a thing.

492
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:20,720
I wondered whether I had tainted your honor,

493
00:31:20,720 --> 00:31:23,850
and I felt guilt for my own helplessness.

494
00:31:29,150 --> 00:31:30,970
I'm sorry.

495
00:31:36,630 --> 00:31:38,450
I...

496
00:31:41,380 --> 00:31:43,010
am fine.

497
00:31:48,020 --> 00:31:49,940
Is that so?

498
00:31:53,330 --> 00:31:57,980
By the way, your sis mentioned she's getting a divorce. She's okay with that?

499
00:31:57,980 --> 00:32:01,300
Yes. Takaya is-

500
00:32:02,770 --> 00:32:05,230
Aoyama is...

501
00:32:08,640 --> 00:32:13,720
That lawyer, your ex-boyfriend, Takaya, is helping her out?

502
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:15,460
I see. I see.

503
00:32:15,460 --> 00:32:19,530
Your ex-boyfriend, Takaya, is much more reliable than me. I see.

504
00:32:19,530 --> 00:32:21,160
I didn't say such a thing.

505
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:24,180
Or it's not Takaya the ex-boyfriend, but current

506
00:32:24,180 --> 00:32:26,470
He's returned to being Takaya the current boyfriend?

507
00:32:26,470 --> 00:32:29,120
What are you talking about? Why would you think that way?

508
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:31,030
The moment we divorced,

509
00:32:31,030 --> 00:32:33,870
you called your ex-boyfriend, Takaya, by his first name!

510
00:32:33,870 --> 00:32:38,300
Cut it out already. A man's jealousy is disgraceful.

511
00:32:39,260 --> 00:32:41,120
Jealousy?

512
00:32:42,080 --> 00:32:44,510
J-Jealousy?

513
00:32:44,510 --> 00:32:46,620
Jealousy?

514
00:32:46,620 --> 00:32:48,800
Sorry.

515
00:32:54,170 --> 00:32:55,690
Jealousy.

516
00:32:56,900 --> 00:32:58,670
Jealousy.

517
00:33:02,030 --> 00:33:03,050
Jealousy!

518
00:33:03,050 --> 00:33:04,950
<i>[M.R Office]</i>

519
00:33:04,950 --> 00:33:07,890
Got it. Arrange for a car, right?

520
00:33:07,890 --> 00:33:09,880
That fancy pen.

521
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:11,820
You're still using it?

522
00:33:11,820 --> 00:33:16,440
You're no longer Saki Obara, but Saki Mizuguchi, aren't you?

523
00:33:16,440 --> 00:33:19,350
Yes, but...

524
00:33:20,020 --> 00:33:23,330
A gift from that rogue samurai?

525
00:33:25,480 --> 00:33:27,790
From the looks of it.

526
00:33:33,650 --> 00:33:36,210
Excuse me.

527
00:33:36,210 --> 00:33:38,070
<i>[You have a new message.]</i>

528
00:33:38,070 --> 00:33:43,900
<i>[Takaya Aoyama: Can we meet sometime? It's regarding Midori.]</i>

